Music producer Chicco Twala appeared in court today, for pointing a suspected firearm at a City Power official. JOHANNESBURG - Music producer Chicco Twala appeared in court on charges of common assault and pointing a suspected firearm at a City Power official. The official was doing repairs in Twala's Bloubosrand neighbourhood on Sunday night when Twala apparently attacked him. Twala alleges he mistook him for a cable thief. READ: Adv. Teffo to sue Police Ministry Twala is father to Longwe Twala, who was in the house with Senzo Meyiwa when he was shot dead in October 2014. In a lengthy message from his cellphone, Twala said he was pleased he had been arrested as it showed he was not above the law. He said it proves to his haters on social media that he does not have the power or money to bribe judges or the Police Minister. Twala was released on R2,000 bail.